  "body": "In the following sample, the SMTChecker correctly recognize there is a problem, but the counter-example it provides is broken: \r\nit suggests: \r\n```\r\n  _x = 0x80 * 2**24\r\n  _y = 2\r\n```\r\nbut this value breaks the \"require\" \r\n\r\n(it does provide a proper counter-example for addition operation, but not for multiplication..)\r\n\r\n```\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0\r\npragma solidity >=0.8.0;\r\n\r\ncontract Overflow {\r\n    uint32 immutable x;\r\n    uint32 immutable y;\r\n\r\n    function mul(uint32 _x, uint32 _y) internal pure returns (uint32) {\r\n        return _x * _y;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    constructor(uint32 _x, uint32 _y) {\r\n\trequire( _y < 50000 );\r\n\trequire( _x < 50000 );\r\n        (x, y) = (_x, _y);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function stateMul() public view returns (uint32) {\r\n        return mul(x, y);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```",
